9. A (1ο). Agrippa Postumus was adopted by Augustus at the same nme with Tiberius in 757, nn. 43 and is styled ‘Agrippa Caesar' in inscriptions (C. 1. On his death, see 1. 6.

Nero Caesar was born probably in the middle ol 759, nn. 6 (see Henzen, p. 6ο), and was betrothed in childhood to a daughter ol Creticus Silanus (a. 43, 3), and married to Julia in 773, nn. ao, on his entry into public lile (3. 19,4). Tacitus describes his character (4. 15 3 59), the plots against him (4. 6ο ; 67), and the lormal charges brought against him (5. 3). 011 these he was banished to Pontia, and subsequently pronounced a public enemy (Suet. Cal. 7) and put to death or compelled to suicide (Suet. Tib. 54), shortly besore the lali ol Seianus. His titles were those oi flamen Augustalis, sodalis Augustalis, sodalis Titius, irater arvalis, fetialis, quaestor. C. 1. L. vi. 913, Lehmann, Claudius, 95-109.
